fields.descriptive_line: Pack of cards, The Game of French History, published in England by Paternoster in 1844
fields.physical_description: Design: letterpress on pink, green or white card; letterpress booklet of rules and a key to the game; card slip case with 2 engraved labels.
fields.title: The ^Game of French History
fields.public_access_description: The 72 cards in this game come in three different colours--pink, green or white, depending on which royal house it belongs to. Each has a brief summary of the events during the reign of French kings. These summaries have gaps in them for the players to fill in. The answers are supplied in a booklet. A personal note on this game is revealed in a hand written inscription which says that 'this belonged to Barbara F B Coventry at the age of 12. She married John Gaspard Fadshaw'.
fields.history_note: A note in ink says that this belonged to Barbara F B Coventry at the age of 12.  She married John Gaspard Fadshaw.
